              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to manipulate or format address data by removing trailing zeros from a given input, which is typically a string representing an address."
        }
