    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is considered low. Scalar functions generally involve straightforward logic, and the task of removing trailing zeros from a string is a simple operation that does not require complex algorithms or data structures."
        }
      ]
    },
